{{zh-forms|[[弱水三千，只取一瓢饮]]|[[弱水三千]]，[[只]][[取]][[一]][[瓢]][[飲]]}}
==Mandarin==
===Etymology===
From: Chapter 91 of the ''[[w:Dream of the Red Chamber|Dream of the Red Chamber]]''
*Literally: (although) the Ruo River is three thousand [[w:li (unit)|li]] long, one only drinks one ladle worth of water from it.
*:Later on, this phrase was used as a [[metaphor]] for choosing only one companion out of all potential mates.

===Idiom===
{{PAGENAME}} (''[[Pinyin]]'' ruòshuĭsānqiān, zhĭ qŭ yì piáo yĭn, ruo4shui3san1qian1zhi3qu3yi4piao2yin3)
# there are so many potential lovers to choose from, but you only pick one from among those potential lovers

